Add an optional vector "frame" to the dock (macOS-style), no background image.

Skins can enable a rounded outline drawn with a QML Rectangle overlaid on the
dock. Its corner radius defaults to the blur radius, so the outline follows the
edge of KWin's native blur region by construction (same blurRadius), and it
scales with the dock (icon count / zoom) like the rest of dockBackground.

The frame is opt-in per skin via new, all-optional Config.qml properties, so
existing skins are unaffected:
  frame        : bool   -- draw the outline
  frameColor   : color  -- outline color (default #59ffffff)
  frameFill    : color  -- interior tint over the blur (default transparent)
  frameBorder  : int    -- outline width in px (default 1)
  frameRadius  : int    -- corner radius (default = blurRadius)
